Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a distributed and heterogeneous computational environment for managing and analyzing large-scale climate simulation data. This involves addressing authentication, authorization, data transport and management, high-performance remote data access, data replication, cataloging, data discovery, distributed monitoring, and web-based portals. These topics are relevant to several computer science sub-categories, including Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Databases (cs.DB), Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE), and Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
